## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Pilo — AI Automation Agent  |  .cursorrules V4.1 (Aligned + Fixed)

## Stack : Next.js 14 App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind

## shadcn/ui · Supabase · Make.com · Resend

## Purpose: Fully aligned with Master Prompt V5.1 (no drift, no conflicts)

## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

---

## 🟢 Frontend Build Mode (ACTIVE PHASE)

* Current phase: Frontend scaffolding
* Backend rules (auth, rate limiting, schemas, webhook execution) are NOT enforced yet
* Use mock data and runAgentDemo for all flows
* Do NOT implement Supabase Auth or Make.com calls
* Use MOCK_USER instead of real session

---

## 🔴 Output Rules (ACTIVE — ALL PHASES)

* Generate ONLY ONE file at a time
* After each file:

  * Verify correctness
  * Ask: "Ready to proceed?"
* Do NOT continue without explicit confirmation
* Do NOT create files outside the defined structure

---

## Project context

* Pilo is an AI-powered automation agent for small business owners.
* Agent uses a ReAct loop: max 5 steps.
* All real tool calls go through Make.com webhooks (backend phase only).

---

## 🔴 Action registry — single source of truth

AllowedActions (MUST match WebhookPayload exactly):

* "Send_Email"
* "Update_Email"
* "Create_Leads"
* "Get_Leads"
* "Delete_Leads"

Rules:

* This list MUST exactly match WebhookPayload in /lib/types.ts
* Never redefine or extend this list anywhere else

Notes:

* "Fallback" is backend-only (Make.com internal)
* Frontend MUST NEVER send "Fallback"

---

## TypeScript rules

* Never use `any`
* No implicit `any` in parameters or variables
* Prefer `type` over `interface`
* All exported functions must have return types
* No non-null assertions

---

## Error handling rules

* console.log / console.warn allowed ONLY for debugging
* NEVER use console logs as a substitute for UI error handling
* All user-facing errors MUST be rendered in UI (EmptyState, Toast, etc.)

---

## 🔴 Single Source of Truth Rule

* Types, actions, and API contracts must have ONE source of truth
* Never duplicate or redefine them across files

---

## 🔴 Agent loop rules (frontend phase)

* Use runAgentDemo.ts for simulation
* Max 5 steps
* Strict sequential execution
* No parallel execution

### Run cancellation (MANDATORY)

* Use cancelRef (useRef<boolean>)
* Set cancelRef.current = true before starting new run
* Reset to false for new run
* Check cancelRef.current BEFORE every appendFeedItem call
* If true → stop execution immediately

---

## 🔴 Demo mode rules

* Demo mode = default
* No external API calls
* No OpenAI calls
* No Make.com calls
* Use deterministic mock responses

### buildDemoFeed placement (MANDATORY)

* buildDemoFeed() MUST be defined in /lib/mockData.ts
* It MUST be exported from mockData.ts
* runAgentDemo.ts MUST import it from mockData
* Never redefine buildDemoFeed elsewhere

---

## 🔴 API rules (frontend phase)

* All API logic lives in /lib/api.ts
* No direct fetch calls inside components

### ApiResponse enforcement

* ALL functions in /lib/api.ts MUST return ApiResponse<T>
* Never return raw data
* Always return { data, error }

---

## 🔴 PiloContext rules

* PiloContext owns ALL global state
* PiloContext owns ALL localStorage interactions for mode ('pilo_mode')

### Mode handling

* ModeToggle MUST call setMode() from context
* ModeToggle MUST NOT access localStorage directly

---

## Frontend rules (STRICT)

* Use Tailwind only

* Use shadcn/ui components

* No custom CSS files

* Components → /components

* Pages → /app

* Utilities → /lib

* Do NOT install new npm packages

* UI must strictly follow prompt design system

* Do NOT invent layouts or styles

---

## 🔴 Feed integrity rules

* Feed must maintain strict chronological order
* No duplicate or out-of-order items

---

## 🔴 Deterministic UI rule

* UI must strictly follow prompt specs
* No creative deviations allowed

---

## Logging rules

* console.log allowed temporarily during development
* Remove before production

---

## Code quality rules

* Target 150–250 lines per file (not strict)
* Extract logic only if reused 3+ times
* Avoid overengineering

---

## TODO rules

* TODO comments allowed in frontend scaffolding
* Replace with GitHub issues before production

---

## Environment rules

* Use mock data in frontend phase
* No environment keys required yet

---

## Git rules

* Commit prefixes: feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:
* Never commit .env files

---

## ✅ Alignment Guarantee

This rulebook is explicitly aligned with:

* Master Prompt V5.1
* Frontend-first build phase

No conflicting instructions exist between prompt and rules.

---

## END OF RULES
